Comment (policies/secretsmanager_confidential_policy_scope.rego:146):
**Wildcard principal double-fires here (low).** `principal_arn` returns `"*"` for a wildcard principal (either bare `"*"` or `{"AWS":"*"}`), and `cleared_principal_arns` will never contain `"*"`, so the same wildcard entry triggers both this `principal_outside_cleared_role_set` finding and `wildcard_principal` at [line 119](policies/secretsmanager_confidential_policy_scope.rego#L119). The wildcard finding is the authoritative one — the cleared-role finding here adds noise without information.

Suggested fix: gate this rule body with `not principal_is_wildcard(principal)` so wildcards are reported once, by the wildcard rule.
