Comment (policies/secretsmanager_privacy_subprocessor_posture.rego:197):
**Wildcard principal double-fires here (low).** Same shape as the confidential-scope policy: `principal_arn` returns `"*"` for a wildcard principal, and `documented_roles_for_vendor_set` will never contain `"*"`, so a wildcard entry fires both this `principal_outside_integration_role_set` finding and `principal_wildcard` at [line 172](policies/secretsmanager_privacy_subprocessor_posture.rego#L172) when the vendor is documented.

Suggested fix: gate this rule body with `not principal_is_wildcard(principal)` so the wildcard rule is the single source of truth for that case.
