Comment (policies/secretsmanager_resource_policy_least_privilege.rego:105):
**Missing `account.account_id` flips cross-account check to false-positive (low).** `account_id` is read via `object.get(account, "account_id", "")` at [line 41](policies/secretsmanager_resource_policy_least_privilege.rego#L41), defaulting to `""`. If the collector ever emits a record without `account.account_id` (partial evidence, a defect, or a manual override), every 12-digit principal account becomes "cross-account" because `principal_account != ""` is always true, and `cross_account_principal_undocumented` fires on every Allow principal.

The same defaulting exists in [secretsmanager_confidential_policy_scope.rego:69](policies/secretsmanager_confidential_policy_scope.rego#L69) (drives `cross_account_principal` at line 128), [secretsmanager_vendor_credential_policy_scope.rego:69](policies/secretsmanager_vendor_credential_policy_scope.rego#L69) (drives `vendor_principal_cross_account_undocumented` at line 152), and [secretsmanager_privacy_transfer_governance.rego:69](policies/secretsmanager_privacy_transfer_governance.rego#L69) (drives the second `cross_border_principal_undocumented` at line 153). One comment to cover the family.

Suggested fix: gate each cross-account violation body with `account_id != ""`, or add a top-level `skip_reason` when `account_id == ""` so missing account evidence does not silently produce findings.
